data.title: Great for volleyball night!
data.text: As far as I know, the main attraction here are the volleyball leagues. We used to go for the exotic animal burgers but they've cut down the menu quite a bit and, sadly, have changed their fries so they aren't as good any more. The duck strips and hush puppies are great and they've got ski-ball so it's still worth a visit!

data.title: A very comfortable "watering hole."
data.text: A very comfortable tavern atmosphere.  Nice place to stop for a drink.  The bar food is fairly good.  I like the gyros (not packaged meat)...real gyros meat.

data.title: Lunch with friends
data.text: Great gyros.   Atmosphere is really good.   Drinks are very reasonable.  We had a great time.   Bartender very attentive.   Will come back again

data.title: A Pleasant Surprise - The Best Fries I've Ever Had!
data.text: Terry's Lounge was actually not our first choice for dinner.  We went to the Roxy for their Friday night fish fry, but the wait was far too long.  My son recommended Terry's and we were pleasantly surprised by the quality of the food.  The wait for the food was longer than it should have been, but the quality of very, very good.  They offer a variety of burger meats.  I had the Kobe been, which was quite good.  Their french fries may be the best I've ever had.  While not strong on ambiance, for a bar food kind of place, it's quite good.  And they have Guinness on tap, which is a big plus!

data.title: Kyle is the best
data.text: I have no friendship or relationship to Kyle but we came in after an afternoon of drinking and we entered a very empty bar. Kyle was on his phone and immediately told the person on the line he had to go.  he made us all the food we ordered with no complaints.  by far, one of the hardest workers on main street. Pay him a visit and you want be disappointed

data.title: Actually Terry's Bar
data.text: Went for lunch.  Had the classic gyro and fries.  Lots of filling and tasted great.  Lots of fries, a meal in itself.  Brother had a hamburger and fries.  Comes a la carte, so you can have whatever you want on it.  He said he really liked the taste.  Great wait staff and great service.  Daily specials at very reasonable prices.  Highly recommended.

data.title: Make sure you have 2 hours to wait.
data.text: It takes so long to get food here, usually about 2 hours.  I like the food a lot but by the time it's ready I don't want it anymore.  Very inattentive staff.   I won't be coming back, tried in twice, same thing both times.
